AWAITING A RADICAL TRANSFORMATION!
Sitting on approximately 1400 square meters of land, is this modest 2 bedroom 1 bathroom beach house. Scattered through the backyard are mature shrubs which are just waiting the creative eye to make the most of their form and create some magic here. The front drive lends itself to improvement however the whole property offers a blank template for you to start your dream!
Whether you are looking to leave a small footprint or expand to something larger, this property ticks the boxes!
Don't wait around, get in quick to view this entry level property!

Description:
PRIME LOCATION WITH WIDE BAY VIEWS
Offered reluctantly for sale is this double storey, well maintained home that you will fall in love with on your first inspection!
Set on a corner allotment in a sought after location and offers 4/5 bedrooms, all with built in robes and ceiling fans. The main feature is the wide water view from the open plan kitchen/living/dining zones and the secure deck.
The main bathroom includes a double shower and is central to all upstairs bedrooms. The home is serviced by a split system and included large windows throughout allowing copious amounts of light to flow though the home.
Dual living opportunity downstairs, fully equipped with 2x rooms, bathroom and kitchenette.
Having a triple garage will accommodate all the family, including their cars and the boat!
Externally the yard is low maintenance with many mature trees and roses with a concrete path surrounding the home. Another bonus is the dual access into the property from Hopkins Drive and also Shepherd Road.
To avoid missing out on this premier property please contact the friendly team at Alex Scott and Staff today!

Description:
COUNTRY COMFORT ON ONE ACRE
Step away from the hustle and bustle and make this striking Queenslander' Style home your own. Set on one private acre of leafy surrounds and well-manicured lawns, with distant French Island and Bay views the property will entice all who come here to relax and just take the peace and country surrounds in.
Excellent colourbond shedding, Asphalted driveway, plenty of parking for the cars, caravan or boat! Even your own pond with jetty. Plenty to love here!
The homestead itself full of character including 3 double sized bedrooms, Master with ensuite, functional kitchen and good sized family room overlooking the gardens. Solid fuel heating and 2 x Reverse Cycle Split systems provide comfort year round.
Presentation plus! Located minutes from Corinella / Coronet Bay townships, Bass Highway for Vline services or shopping in Grantville and just 40 minutes to Cranbourne - Make the discovery for yourself today.

Description:
Stunning family home just a few steps from Grantville beach
Beach lovers will delight in this propertys position, where within a few minutes stroll you can have your toes planted in golden sands and glistening waters, or simply sit and watch the stunning sunsets.
This beautifully presented home will capture you the minute you enter. Inside begins with a welcoming and spacious open plan living and dining area which evokes a sense of relaxed beachside tranquillity with water views. The kitchen is well appointed with all new SS appliances. A split system reverse cycle air conditioner and wood fire heater ensure the living spaces can be comfortable year-round. The home comprises three bedrooms with new carpet and built in robes, with the Master featuring an ensuite and large walk-in robe.
Moving outside, the enclosed backyard offers a low maintenance garden with double remote-control garage and 5000L water tank.
This home is situated on a corner block providing easy access to the back yard for a boat or caravan.
You are surrounded by all the Bass Coast region has to offer from tourist attractions, restaurants, cafes, local markets, Church Hill Island Heritage Farm, Phillip Island and much more.
Daniel & Tamara proudly present this amazing home to you please call to view if you are unable to attend the Open For Inspections

Description:
MOTIVATED VENDOR - OFFERS WANTED!
On offer is this spacious and comfortable elevated home on large block over 1,200 sq.m. under 500 metres to foreshore. So if you are looking for a seaside change or investment take a look at this property which is priced to sell. Featuring - 4 bedrooms all with b/i/r/s - Open plan living/meals/ kitchen area - Sliding doors from living to large deck - Family bathroom - En suite to master with corner spa bath - Freshly painted interior - New carpet throughout - Plenty of room for caravan, boat or extra vehicles.
Tenby Point is a quaint and secluded no through road leading to the waters edge with farmland at rear of properties. Relax on the back deck and enjoy the kookaburras and wildlife that makes this property an escape from city living. Take a stroll along the beach or go fishing from the rocks. There is also a 24 hour boat ramp/jetty only a couple of minutes at Corinella plus general shop, café, community centre, tennis courts, lawn bowls and hall. At the corner of Tenby Point there is a school bus stop and another 5 mins a group of shops with doctor, chemist, bank, ambulance depot , newsagency and cafes. Phillip Island and major shopping centre 25 mins and easy commute to CBD with dual lane highway. This is an ideal family residence.

Description:
FABULOUS HOBBY FARM- APPROXIMATELY 600 METERS FROM THE WATER - AND OFFERS 2 ROAD FRONTAGES
In the heart of Grantville, these wonderful 4 acres (approxamatly) offer the perfect space for family, horses or other pets. The land is fully fenced and boasts 3 paddocks, shedding, a dam, loads of fruit trees and plenty of room for trucks, boat caravans, floats. The property is zoned low-density residential, with the potential to subdivide (STCA) and offers 2 road frontages.
The 1950s country style farm home, offers flexible living to accommodate the family, 4 bedrooms, 3 bathrooms and located within minutes of shops, transport, and public schools.
This complete package offers a wonderful rural lifestyle with the convenience of living close to amenities. If you are after versatile affordable acres with a great outlook and potential, come and have a look at this one.

Description:
Old Cottage - Court Location!!!
This property is in need of lots and lots of work or you may later decide in the future to demolish and build a new home.
So to inspect remove those rose coloured glasses!!!!!
The dwelling consists of 4 good size rooms consisting of a spacious kitchen, lounge room, bedroom, sitting room and there is separate bathroom, laundry and toilet.
Features include hardwood flooring, open fire place, split-system air conditioner , old shed and is fully fenced.
Located very close to the newly revamped 24 hour boat ramp and only a stroll away from the foreshore walking tracks. All the amenities are in place and the property has established gardens and plenty of room for the caravan and boat. This is a prime location in a developing community and with some imagination and hard work could make the perfect fisherman shack or getaway.
Local shops, primary school and day care centre are only 7 minutes away, major shopping centre and Phillip Island approx. 25 mins.
Easy commute to CBD with dual lane highway.

Description:
ELEVATED WITH WATER VIEW AND A PLUNGE POOL!
We welcome your inspection at this truly fantastic property. Offering prime location on the Eastern side of the street, capturing views across Westernport Bay to French Island, Phillip Island, Bass Coast shoreline and on a clear day you will see Melbourne CBD from the front entertainers deck!
The property itself has lovely landscaped gardens with large steps leading you up to the private rear garden which houses a plunge pool and separate zones for the avid entertainer. The house itself has had good improvements throughout whilst keeping its charm of yesteryear with quirky choices of colour to the kitchen cabinets, white deco wood heater, updated light/fan combinations and an internal layout which needs to be seen to really be appreciated.
Currently the home is used as a three bedroom, one bathroom property with two good living areas. One of which is downstairs and offers many uses including 4th bedroom or gym. Or step outside the box and set your home business up here, with plenty of natural light and opportunity to further expand on the existing space the opportunities are really only limited by your imagination!
This home has been well cared for and is a credit to its current owners. Your inspection of this highly sought after property will not disappoint! Contact the team at Alex Scott & Staff Bass Valley today to arrange your inspection on 5678 8433.

A Property With Options

The kitchen is cupboard packed, with built in additional storage cabinets and overhead cupboards. A gas upright cooker, gas wall furnace and island benchtop. Master bedroom and third bedroom have built in robes, no robes in 2nd bedroom, hallway with loads of additional storage cupboards. Lovely renovated bright bathroom with new bath and shower over the bath, new vanity, basin and beautifully tiled. There is also a second shower and vanity. Separate laundry with new trough and separate toilet. Large garage/shed/workshop, water tanks. Property connected to gas bottles. Currently leased for $500 per week, including 15 acres of land at the rear property 144 Settlement Rd. Lease ends 05/10/19

Description:
Family Living on 1005sqm With Side Access
This beautiful family home really has something for everyone. With a sizable 34 sq (approx) residence boasting 4 bedrooms plus a study, 2 bathrooms, a large open plan kitchen, living and dining as well as a theatre room outside is a large entertainers deck, wide side access to a man-sized shed and fully enclosed backyard. Only 2 years old, all the hard work with building has been done for you. Move in, relax and enjoy this as-good-as-new property.
Inside you are greeted by a wide and sprawling open entry and hallway. The master is big and spacious and complemented by a walk-in robe, ceiling fan and lavish ensuite with full double shower, large vanity with stone bench tops and quality fittings. The remaining bedrooms are all well-proportioned, with built-in robes and ceiling fans and are serviced by a separate powder room and bright and practical family bathroom with rainwater shower head and stone bench tops.
Entertain the kids or enjoy the football in the separate theatre room, or sit and relax in the open plan family room. This clever floorplan also offers a tucked away home office perfect for peace and quiet to work from home, away from the noise of family.
The chef's kitchen is a dream for the entertainers with a large island bench with 40mm waterfall stone bench tops, 900mm free-standing stainless-steel stove and dishwasher. A double under-mount sink creates clean lines while the butler's pantry offers plenty of extra bench space, fridge space and plentiful cabinetry all cleverly tucked away from view.
Outside is a car lovers dream, with huge nature strip and set back creating additional off-street parking as well as a wide side-access to the backyard and the shed. Featuring extra car storage, plus work shop, the roller doors are extra high to cater for boats, caravans and all the toys.
A large rear deck is the perfect summer entertaining zone, with double stacker sliding doors granting access from the kitchen/living and full site from the kitchen.
Additional features include Ducted heating, evaporative cooling, double glazed windows.
All set on a fully-enclosed 1005sqm (approx) block and surrounded by larger properties giving the illusion of space whilst still being walking distance to Lang Lang shops, school and public transport.
Please Note: Photo ID is required for all inspections.
